Baku Metro.label: Baku Metro
Baku Metro.description: Baku Metro is a rapid transit system serving Baku, the capital of Azerbaijan. First opened on November 6, 1967, during the time of the Soviet Union, it has the features found in most other ex-Soviet ... Wikipedia

Berlin S-Bahn.label: Berlin S-Bahn
Berlin S-Bahn.description: The Berlin S-Bahn is a rapid transit railway system in and around Berlin, the capital city of Germany. Wikipedia

Dorfbahn Serfaus.label: Dorfbahn Serfaus
Dorfbahn Serfaus.description: The Dorfbahn Serfaus is an unusual underground air cushion funicular transit system in the Tyrolian village of Serfaus in Austria. The name literally translates as Serfaus Village Railway. Wikipedia

Genoa Metro.label: Genoa Metro
Genoa Metro.description: The Genoa Metro is a light metro consisting of a single line that connects the centre of Genoa, Italy with the suburb of Rivarolo Ligure, to the north-west of the city centre. Wikipedia

FirstGroup.label: FirstGroup
FirstGroup.description: FirstGroup is a British transport group, registered and operating in the United Kingdom. The company also operate transport services in Ireland, Denmark, Canada and the United States. Wikipedia

Greyhound Lines.label: Greyhound Lines
Greyhound Lines.description: Greyhound Lines, Inc., called Greyhound for short, is an intercity bus service common carrier serving over 3,700 destinations in the United States, Canada, and Mexico. Wikipedia

Hamburg S-Bahn.label: Hamburg S-Bahn
Hamburg S-Bahn.description: The Hamburg S-Bahn is rapid mass transit railway network in the Hamburg Metropolitan Region. Together, the S-Bahn, the Hamburg U-Bahn, the AKN railway and the regional railway form the backbone of ... Wikipedia

Ho Chi Minh City Metro.label: Ho Chi Minh City Metro
Ho Chi Minh City Metro.description: The Ho Chi Minh City Metro is a proposed rapid transit network that will serve Ho Chi Minh City in Vietnam. Wikipedia

Japanese National Railways.label: Japanese National Railways
Japanese National Railways.description: Japanese National Railways, abbreviated Kokutetsu or "JNR", was the body which operated the national railway network of Japan from 1949 to 1987. Wikipedia

Keretapi Tanah Melayu.label: Keretapi Tanah Melayu
Keretapi Tanah Melayu.description: Keretapi Tanah Melayu Berhad or Malayan Railways Limited is the main rail operator in Peninsular Malaysia. The railway system dates back to the British colonial era, when it was first built to transport tin. Wikipedia

Kiev Metro.label: Kiev Metro
Kiev Metro.description: The Kiev Metro is a metro system that is the mainstay of Kiev's public transport. It was the first rapid transit system in Ukraine and the third one built in the USSR. It now has three lines with a total length of 66.6 kilometres and 52 stations. Wikipedia

Kobe Municipal Subway.label: Kobe Municipal Subway
Kobe Municipal Subway.description: Kobe Municipal Subway is the subway of Kobe. It has two lines. Wikipedia

Lima Metro.label: Lima Metro
Lima Metro.description: The Lima Metro, colloquially referred to as El Tren Eléctrico by Lima residents, is a metropolitan railway currently linking south Lima with the centre of the capital of Peru. Wikipedia

Mariazell Railway.label: Mariazell Railway
Mariazell Railway.description: The Mariazell Railway is an electrically operated narrow-gauge railway which connects the Lower Austrian capital Sankt Pölten with the Styrian pilgrimage centre of Mariazell. Wikipedia

Memphis Suspension Railway.label: Memphis Suspension Railway
Memphis Suspension Railway.description: The Memphis Suspension Railway or Mud Island Monorail is a suspended monorail that connects the city center of Memphis with the entertainment park on Mud Island. Wikipedia

Mount Washington Cog Railway.label: Mount Washington Cog Railway
Mount Washington Cog Railway.description: The Mount Washington Cog Railway is the world's first mountain-climbing cog railway. The railway is still in operation, climbing Mount Washington in New Hampshire, USA. Wikipedia

Poma 2000.label: Poma 2000
Poma 2000.description:
The Poma 2000 in Laon, France, is an automated guideway transit, a cable-driven people mover which runs between the railway station and the city hall.
There are three stations. Wikipedia

Serbian Railways.label: Serbian Railways
Serbian Railways.description: Serbian Railways is the national railway company of Serbia. Serbian Railways is a member of the International Union of Railways. The UIC Country Code for Serbia is 72. Wikipedia

Tünel.label: Tünel
Tünel.description: The Tünel is a short underground railway line in Istanbul, Turkey. It is an underground funicular with two stations, connecting the quarters of Karaköy and Beyoğlu. Wikipedia

TransMilenio.label: TransMilenio
TransMilenio.description: TransMilenio is a bus rapid transit system that serves Bogotá, the capital of Colombia. The system opened to the public in December 2000, covering Av. Caracas and Calle 80. Wikipedia

Budapest Metro.label: Budapest Metro
Budapest Metro.description: The Budapest Metro is the rapid transit system in the Hungarian capital Budapest. It is the oldest electrified underground railway system on the European continent, and the second-oldest in Europe, ... Wikipedia

Metro Bilbao.label: Metro Bilbao
Metro Bilbao.description: The Bilbao Metro, trademarked as Metro Bilbao, is a rapid transit system serving the city of Bilbao and the region of Greater Bilbao. Wikipedia

Osaka Monorail.label: Osaka Monorail
Osaka Monorail.description: The Osaka Monorail is a monorail in northern Osaka Prefecture, Japan, operated by Osaka Monorail Co., Ltd.. Wikipedia

Hankyu Railway.label: Hankyu Railway
Hankyu Railway.description: Hankyu Railway, commonly known as Hankyū Dentetsu, is a Japanese private railway that provides commuter and interurban service to the northern Kansai region and is one of major businesses operated by Hankyu Hanshin Holdings, Inc. Wikipedia

White Pass and Yukon Route.label: White Pass and Yukon Route
White Pass and Yukon Route.description: The White Pass and Yukon Route is a Canadian and U.S. Class II 3 ft narrow gauge railroad linking the port of Skagway, Alaska, with Whitehorse, the capital of Yukon. An isolated system, it has no direct connection to any other railroad. Wikipedia

Atlantic City Railroad.label: Atlantic City Railroad
Atlantic City Railroad.description: The Atlantic City Railroad was a Philadelphia and Reading Railway subsidiary that became part of Pennsylvania-Reading Seashore Lines in 1933. Wikipedia

Chemin de Fer Moudania Brousse.label: Chemin de Fer Moudania Brousse
Chemin de Fer Moudania Brousse.description: The Chemin de Fer Moudania Brousse, or CFMB was a 41-kilometre long railway line from the port of Mudanya to Bursa. Wikipedia

El Paso and Northeastern Railway.label: El Paso and Northeastern Railway
El Paso and Northeastern Railway.description: The El Paso and Northeastern Railway was a short line railroad that was built around the beginning of the twentieth century to help connect the industrial and commercial center at El Paso, Texas, with ... Wikipedia

Aberystwyth Cliff Railway.label: Aberystwyth Cliff Railway
Aberystwyth Cliff Railway.description: The Aberystwyth Cliff Railway is a funicular railway in Aberystwyth, Ceredigion, Wales. Opened in 1896 at 778 feet in length, it was the longest funicular railway in the British Isles, since surpassed ... Wikipedia

Maryland Central Railroad.label: Maryland Central Railroad
Maryland Central Railroad.description: The Maryland Central Railroad was a 19th-century 3 ft narrow gauge railroad in Maryland, with a small track section in Pennsylvania. It operated freight and passenger trains between Baltimore and Delta, Pennsylvania. Wikipedia

Albany and Susquehanna Railroad.label: Albany and Susquehanna Railroad
Albany and Susquehanna Railroad.description: The Albany and Susquehanna Railroad was a 6 ft broad gauge railroad running from Albany to Binghamton, New York, operating 1851 to 1870. Wikipedia

Atlantic and Pacific Railroad.label: Atlantic and Pacific Railroad
Atlantic and Pacific Railroad.description: The Atlantic and Pacific Railroad was a U.S. railroad that owned or operated two disjointed segments, one connecting St. Louis, Missouri with Tulsa, Oklahoma, and the other connecting Albuquerque, New Mexico with Southern California. Wikipedia

California High-Speed Rail.label: California High-Speed Rail
California High-Speed Rail.description: The California High-Speed Rail project is a planned high-speed rail system in the state of California to be run by the California High-Speed Rail Authority, commonly referred to simply as the Authority. Wikipedia

Beer Heights Light Railway.label: Beer Heights Light Railway
Beer Heights Light Railway.description: The Beer Heights Light Railway operates 1-mile of minimum gauge 7 ¹⁄4 in track at Beer, Devon, England. It is part of Pecorama, an exhibition owned by Peco. Wikipedia

Capital City Street Railway.label: Capital City Street Railway
Capital City Street Railway.description: The Capital City Street Railway, also known as the Lightning Route, was the first city-wide system of streetcars established in Montgomery, Alabama, United States on April 15, 1886. Wikipedia

Carson and Colorado Railway.label: Carson and Colorado Railway
Carson and Colorado Railway.description: The Carson and Colorado Railway was a U.S. 3 ft narrow gauge railroad that ran from Mound House, Nevada, to Keeler, California below the Cerro Gordo Mines. Wikipedia

Chemins de Fer Syriens.label: Syrian Railways
Chemins de Fer Syriens.description: General Establishment of Syrian Railways is the national railway operator for the state of Syria, subordinate to the Ministry of Transportation. It was established in 1956 and is headquartered in Aleppo. Wikipedia

Disneyland Railroad.label: Disneyland Railroad
Disneyland Railroad.description: The Disneyland Railroad, originally the Santa Fe & Disneyland Railroad, is a 3 ft narrow gauge railroad at Disneyland, Anaheim, California, United States, that was inaugurated on the park's live television preview on July 17, 1955. Wikipedia

East Broad Top Railroad and Coal Company.label: East Broad Top Railroad and Coal Company
East Broad Top Railroad and Coal Company.description: The East Broad Top Railroad and Coal Company is a for-profit, 3 ft narrow gauge historic railroad headquartered in Rockhill Furnace, Pennsylvania, 19 miles north of Interstate 76 and 11 miles south of U.S. Route 22, the William Penn Highway. Wikipedia
